docs.abstract: The chip maker claims Apple wanted to reduce its reliance on Qualcomm technology and make sure Intel’s chips were just as good.

docs.abstract: Hundreds of McDonald’s employees rallied to demand that the largest fast food chain in the country do more to combat sexual harassment in the workplace.
docs.snippet: Hundreds of McDonald’s employees rallied to demand that the largest fast food chain in the country do more to combat sexual harassment in the workplace.
docs.lead_paragraph: In a St. Louis suburb, they chanted, “Hold your burgers, hold your fries. Keep your hands off my thighs.” In Chicago, they had blue duct tape that said “MeToo” covering their mouths. And in Kansas City, Mo., they held signs bearing the same anti-sexual harassment hashtag with the first letter styled to look like the McDonald’s golden arches.

headline.main: McDonald’s Workers Across the U.S. Stage #MeToo Protests

headline.main: Why Jeff Bezos Should Push for Nobody to Get as Rich as Jeff Bezos
headline.print_headline: How Bezos Can Help Prevent the Next Bezos

docs.abstract: The European Union’s antitrust chief announced an inquiry into the e-commerce giant over its use of data collected about third-party merchants.
docs.snippet: The European Union’s antitrust chief announced an inquiry into the e-commerce giant over its use of data collected about third-party merchants.
docs.lead_paragraph: For many independent merchants who sell their goods on Amazon, there has long been deep concern that if the e-commerce giant saw a particular product selling well, the company would duplicate it, but at a lower price.

headline.main: Amazon Dominates as a Merchant and Platform. Europe Sees Reason to Worry.
headline.print_headline: Europe to Investigate Amazon’s Dual Role of Merchant and Platform
